concept_explanation.log_levels:
**Choosing the right log level:**

```java
// ERROR: something failed that needs attention NOW
log.error("Payment failed paymentId={} gateway={} errorCode={}", paymentId, gateway, errorCode);

// WARN: degraded but not broken (circuit open, fallback used)
log.warn("Using cached price for symbol={} reason=feed_timeout", symbol);

// INFO: significant business events
log.info("Payment processed paymentId={} amount={} userId={}", paymentId, amount, userId);

// DEBUG: technical details (disabled in production)
log.debug("Entering validateCard cardType={} token={}", cardType, token);

// TRACE: extremely verbose (disabled always in prod)
log.trace("DB query took={}ms rows={}", queryTime, rows);

// PRODUCTION levels: ERROR + WARN in most packages, INFO for business logic
// logging.level.com.razorpay: INFO
// logging.level.org.springframework: WARN
// logging.level.com.zaxxer.hikari: WARN
// NEVER: log passwords, card numbers, PAN, API keys — log.info("Charging {}", cardNumber) is a BREACH
```

